<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:scilab="http://www.scilab.org" xml:id="m2sci_fopen">
    <refnamediv>
        <refname>fopen (Matlab function)</refname>
        <refpurpose>Open a file or obtain information about open files</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>
    <refsection>
        <title>Matlab/Scilab equivalent</title>
        <informaltable border="1" width="100%">
            <tr>
                <td align="center">
                    <emphasis role="bold">Matlab</emphasis>
                </td>
                <td align="center">
                    <emphasis role="bold">Scilab</emphasis>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>
                    <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
fopen
]]></programlisting>
                </td>
                <td>
                    <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
mopen
]]></programlisting>
                </td>
            </tr>
        </informaltable>
    </refsection>
    <refsection>
        <title>Particular cases</title>
        <variablelist>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>Access permission:</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        Matlab offers two permissions options not supported by Scilab: <emphasis role="bold">W</emphasis> and <emphasis role="bold">A</emphasis> (for tape drives) 
                    </para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>Input values:</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        In Matlab, <emphasis role="bold">fopen('all')</emphasis> lists all opened files, in Scilab, this type of call for <emphasis role="bold">fopen</emphasis> does not exist. You can also use <emphasis role="bold">fopen</emphasis> in Matlab to get information on a file identifier (<emphasis role="bold">fopen(fid)</emphasis>), this case is not implemented in Scilab.
                    </para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>Machine format:</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        Note that Scilab does not support machine format values as input or output.
                    </para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
        <para>
            Matlab <emphasis role="bold">fopen</emphasis> can return an error message but not Scilab <emphasis role="bold">mopen</emphasis>, moreover, returned file identifier is <emphasis role="bold">-1</emphasis> in case of error in Matlab but does not exist in this case in Scilab, so an emulation function has been written <emphasis role="bold">mtlb_fopen</emphasis>.
        </para>
    </refsection>
</refentry>
